          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>2 fol. on parchment; Shelfmark: Marcel 123; Qurʾānic Text: Q 101:5-103:1; 5 lines per page; Dimensions:  315 x 196mm; Script style: kūfi D.III.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>The fragments <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/2280/page/1r">Marcel 64</ref> and <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/2287/page/1r">Marcel 68</ref> (NLR) have a similar handwriting and illumination.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>The catalogue entry by Valery V. Polosin (1939-2014) contains the following information:</p>
              <p/>
              <p>"<hi rend="bold">Marcel 123</hi></p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">F</hi><hi rend="bold">ragment</hi>: <hi rend="bold">101</hi>:4(5)–<hi rend="bold">102</hi>:8(8)*, <hi rend="bold">103</hi> (только заглавие).</p>
              <p>2 fol. 195/197×315 mm (1.62). <hi rend="bold">Support</hi>: thin and transparent parchment, rigid, smooth of yellowish color (especially in the hair side).<hi rend="bold"> Writing</hi><hi rend="bold"> </hi><hi rend="bold">material</hi>: dark brown ink.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Collation</hi>: one bifolium, F1H / H2F<hi rend="italic"> </hi>.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Text layout</hi>: 108×192 mm (1.777), 5 lines. <hi rend="bold">Ruling</hi>: absent.<hi rend="bold"> </hi><hi rend="bold">Script</hi>: D III.<hi rend="bold"> Diacritics</hi>: absent.<hi rend="bold"> Vocalization</hi>: red, green, orange and blue round dots.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Verse markers</hi>: for groups of individual verses – teardrop-shaped medallions (type 4.1.1), in gold and green paint, surrounded with petals drawn in ink with red dots between them, with the inscribed word اية; for groups of 5 verses – lobed medallions in the line or over it (type 3.С.II), in gold and colors, with the inscribed word خمس (fol. 1r, 2r).</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Surah titles</hi> written in gold with palmettos in the margin drawn in gold, red ad green paint; fol. 1v – surah 102 (التكاثر ثمان), fol. 2v – surah 103 (العصرثلاث ايات); in the medallion on fol. 2v the number of the last verso of the preceding surah is inscribed (احد عشر).<hi rend="underline"/></p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Inscriptions</hi>: numbers of surahs in Roman numerals and the verse numbers in Arabic numerals are inscribed in pencil on the upper margin of all pages (on verso pages also on the lower margins); numbers of verses are also marked in the text.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Defects</hi>: minor stains; par of the lower margin next to the spine is cut out; upper margins completely cut off; on all the pages there are imprints of ink from the opposite pages. </p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Old accession numbers</hi>: (according to Langlois’ 2<hi rend="superscript">nd</hi> inventory).</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Contents</hi>:</p>
              <p>Fol. 1r–1v. Surah 101, verses 4(5)–8(11)*. Incipit: [المنفو]ش * فاما من ثقلت.</p>
              <p>Fol. 2r–2v. Surah 102. Explicit: [النعيم {...} [بسم اللهٍ .</p>
              <p>Fol. 2v. Surah 103, only title.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Other fragments of the same manuscript</hi>: Arabe 351 (BNF); MSS Marcel 64 and Marcel 68 (NLR) have similar handwriting and illumination."</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>Olga Yastrebova has translated and sometimes corrected the notes of V. Polosin. Corrected passages are marked with ОЯ (O.Ya).</p>
            </summary>
